AGENTS.md:145:+ **DooD sibling containers survive SIGKILL of the local `docker run` client; the cidfile-driven `post_kill_callback` is load-bearing.** Killing the local `docker run` process via `os.killpg(SIGKILL)` does NOT propagate to the spawned container — the daemon parent keeps it running until the workload exits or it's killed externally. Plans that wrap `subprocess.Popen` with `docker run` must register a `post_kill_callback` (stored on the `Subprocess` instance, fires on the SIGKILL escalation branch) that reads the cidfile and runs `docker kill && docker rm -f`. The cleanup callback that unlinks the cidfile must run on **every** terminal exit branch (graceful, fast-path, and SIGKILL) — not just SIGKILL — because `--cidfile` errors if the path exists, so cidfile reuse without cleanup is a hard failure. See [`reference/services/_common/src/eden_service_common/container_exec.py`](reference/services/_common/src/eden_service_common/container_exec.py) and the §D.3 design notes in [`docs/plans/eden-phase-10d-followup-a-container-isolation.md`](docs/plans/eden-phase-10d-followup-a-container-isolation.md).
